        <mxCell id="p1-vpc" parent="p1-cloud" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#EFF7EF,#162316);strokeColor=#3F8624;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=12;fontColor=#3F8624;fontFamily=Helvetica;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=6;" value="VPC vpc-0ca4ed8dda6c888f1 + DNS Firewall (egress allowlist)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="1280" x="410" y="790" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1-vpc-n" parent="p1-vpc" style="text;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#3F8624;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=6;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Gateway &amp; Interface Endpoints:&lt;/b&gt; DynamoDB · ECR · ECR-Docker · CloudWatch Logs · Secrets Manager · Bedrock Runtime · STS · X-Ray&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;DNS Firewall:&lt;/b&gt; restrict egress from agent containers. Allowlist: anthropic.com, github.com, pypi.org, registry.npmjs.org (see cdk/src/constructs/dns-firewall.ts).&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;AgentCore Runtime:&lt;/b&gt; uses VPC indirectly via CloudWatch ADOT sidecar for X-Ray tracing. MicroVMs themselves are managed by AgentCore.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;KMS:&lt;/b&gt; CMKs encrypt DDB tables + log groups at rest." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="140" width="1240" x="20" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1-agentnote" parent="p1-cloud" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E0F2F1,#0d2838);strokeColor=#01A88D;strokeWidth=1.5;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=11;fontColor=#01A88D;fontFamily=Helvetica;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=4;" value="Agent code (inside Docker container, Python 3.14) — shared by both runtimes" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="1280" x="410" y="1000" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1-agentnote-n" parent="p1-agentnote" style="text;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#01A88D;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=6;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;server.py&lt;/b&gt; — ASGI. /invocations (sync JSON → spawn bg thread · SSE → drain asyncio.Queue, attach-don&#39;t-spawn multi-subscriber registry · 15s keepalive). /ping → HealthyBusy while task active.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;pipeline.py → runner.py&lt;/b&gt; — ClaudeSDKClient.query loop. Sync bg thread. Emits dual to ProgressWriter + SSEAdapter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;progress_writer.py&lt;/b&gt; (1a) — PutItem TaskEventsTable. Fail-open + circuit breaker. ULID event_id. Durability layer.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;sse_adapter.py + sse_wire.py&lt;/b&gt; (1b) — per-session asyncio.Queue; pure-function AG-UI frame translator.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;hooks.py&lt;/b&gt; — PreToolUse (Cedar engine ALLOW/DENY) · PostToolUse (output_scanner.py redacts secrets/PII) · Stop hook ⭐ (between-turns registry — &lt;code&gt;_nudge_between_turns_hook&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;⭐ nudge_reader.py (Phase 2)&lt;/b&gt; — Query TaskNudgesTable consumed=false → conditional UpdateItem mark consumed (ExpressionAttributeNames: #c=consumed reserved keyword) → format as &amp;lt;user_nudge&amp;gt; XML → return via Stop hook `{decision:block, reason:xml}` so SDK treats as next user message.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;policy.py&lt;/b&gt; — Cedar engine (Phase 3 foundation; currently ALLOW/DENY only).&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Design note:&lt;/b&gt; the between-turns-hooks registry is intentionally extensible — Phase 2.5 mid-turn-interrupt and Phase 3 Cedar HITL will both plug in here without refactoring the pipeline." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="240" width="1240" x="20" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p1-iot-note" parent="p1-cloud" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFDE7,#2a2a14);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#6B4E00,#FFD180);spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;CDK custom resources (not application Lambdas):&lt;/b&gt; CustomVpcRestrictDefaultSGCustomResourceProvider, AWS-CR handler for SSM params. Not shown individually; see cdk/test/ for coverage." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="1280" x="410" y="1300" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
