        <mxCell id="p5m16" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;" value="15. invoke">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1820" y="1035" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="1640" y="1035" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p5m17" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;" value="Query(PK=task_id, SK &gt; after)">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1820" y="1070" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="1640" y="1070" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p5m18" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#C925D1;" value="16. return events since last_event_id">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1820" y="1110" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="110" y="1110" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p5m19" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#2E7D32;fontStyle=1;" value="17. RUN_FINISHED seen → CLI exits 0 (PR URL from terminal event)">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1820" y="1200" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="110" y="1200" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p5n1" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=14;fillColor=light-dark(#E3F2FD,#0d2238);strokeColor=#1F6FEB;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#1F6FEB;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="Why no SSE on this path?&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;Runtime-IAM&#39;s microVM never activates sse_adapter.py because server.py&#39;s SSE path is only taken when Accept: text/event-stream. Orchestrator uses Accept: application/json. So even if a client tried SSE to Runtime-JWT for this task, the server-side RUN_ELSEWHERE guard (409) prevents cross-runtime observation.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1250" width="1020" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p5n2" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=14;fillColor=light-dark(#FFECB3,#3a2e10);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="15-min Lambda cap vs 8h agent session&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;After OrchestratorFn hits its 15-min cap, the Lambda invocation ends. AgentCore keeps the microVM alive (up to 8h maxLifetime). ProgressWriter keeps writing to TaskEventsTable. The watch client polls DDB — nothing to do with the Lambda — so the user sees events continuously. Long tasks (&gt;15 min) are one reason polling is the correct transport here.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="1250" width="1040" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram name="6. SSE reconnection flow (60-min cap, network drop, cross-client)" id="v5p6">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1938" dy="780" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="0" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2000" pageHeight="1800" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
