          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7m20" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;fontStyle=1;" value="19. Stop hook returns {decision: &quot;block&quot;, reason: &quot;&lt;user_nudge&gt;...&lt;/user_nudge&gt;&quot;}">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1410" y="1115" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="1220" y="1115" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7note-sdk" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E0F2F1,#0d2838);strokeColor=#01A88D;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="SDK contract: `decision=&quot;block&quot;` + `reason` → Claude Agent SDK treats `reason` as the NEXT USER MESSAGE. The agent&#39;s next turn incorporates the &lt;user_nudge&gt; XML content as if the user had typed it. No special tool, no out-of-band signal — just reuse the standard turn mechanism." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1140" width="2300" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7m21" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;" value="20. SDK begins next turn with the nudged content as user message">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1220" y="1215" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="1220" y="1240" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7m22" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;labelBackgroundColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;fontStyle=1;" value="21. Terminal A sees agent&#39;s response acknowledging/acting on the nudge (live)">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="1220" y="1265" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="1950" y="1265" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7n1" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=14;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#C925D1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="At-most-once delivery&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;ConditionExpression `#c = :false` guarantees that even if the Stop hook fires twice concurrently (e.g. tool-call race), only ONE invocation successfully marks the row consumed. The other gets ConditionalCheckFailedException and ignores the row. No double-delivery.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1320" width="700" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7n2" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=14;fillColor=light-dark(#FFECB3,#3a2e10);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="Why not mid-turn?&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;Phase 2 consumes at between-turns seams only. If the agent is running a long Bash command (5 min) or a big Edit, the nudge waits. This is an explicit design tradeoff for turn atomicity + side-effect safety. Phase 2.5 (see next page) adds mid-turn interrupt via ClaudeSDKClient.interrupt() but with caveats about partial side effects.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="1320" width="760" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7n3" parent="1" style="shape=note;size=14;fillColor=light-dark(#E3F2FD,#0d2238);strokeColor=#1F6FEB;html=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#1F6FEB;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="Works on BOTH runtimes&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;This flow is identical whether the agent is on Runtime-IAM (orchestrator path) or Runtime-JWT (direct SSE). The only difference: on Runtime-IAM there&#39;s no sse_adapter side, so step 17b is a no-op and step 18 doesn&#39;t happen — Terminal A polling picks up the nudge_acknowledged event from DDB on the next poll cycle (~500ms).&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1540" y="1320" width="800" height="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram name="8. Pending — Phase 1c WebSocket upgrade (proposal)" id="v5p8">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2000" dy="1200" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="0" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2200" pageHeight="1500" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="p8t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;" value="Pending — Phase 1c: WebSocket upgrade (proposal, only if SSE proves insufficient)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="20" width="2100" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=13;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#555555;" value="Add `/ws` sub-resource on AgentCore Runtime-JWT alongside existing `/invocations`. Same AG-UI event schema server→client, but adds bidirectional client→server frames (for mid-turn signals). REST/SSE stay; WebSocket sits alongside. Design per §9.1.1 D1 D2 D3 (alternatives rejected in page 11). This is a PROPOSAL only — trigger to build is real production signal that SSE latency or cross-client sharing is a user-felt limitation." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="62" width="2100" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8bar" parent="1" style="line;strokeWidth=2;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeDasharray=8 4;html=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="120" width="2100" height="10" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8current" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#C8E6C9,#1c361d);strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=16;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="CURRENT (Phase 1b shipped) — SSE only" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="150" width="1000" height="620" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-cli" parent="p8current" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#232F3E;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="bgagent CLI&#xa;EventSource /invocations" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="70" width="230" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-rt" parent="p8current" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E0F2F1,#0d2838);strokeColor=#01A88D;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;container=1;collapsible=0;" value="Runtime-JWT microVM" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="340" y="70" width="600" height="500" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-srv" parent="p8c-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="server.py&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;POST /invocations&lt;br&gt;Accept: text/event-stream&lt;br&gt;→ drain asyncio.Queue → SSE frames&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="40" width="260" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-pipe" parent="p8c-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="pipeline.py / runner.py&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Sync bg thread. ClaudeSDKClient.query loop. Emits dual to progress_writer + sse_adapter.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="170" width="260" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-hooks" parent="p8c-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="hooks.py&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Stop hook: between_turns_hooks registry.&lt;br&gt;_nudge_between_turns_hook reads TaskNudgesTable (REST-submitted).&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="310" y="40" width="260" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-nudge-flow" parent="p8c-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#C925D1;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Nudge delivery path (current)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;1. REST POST /tasks/{id}/nudge&lt;br&gt;2. NudgeTaskFn → TaskNudgesTable&lt;br&gt;3. Stop hook reads between turns&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Extra hop:&lt;/b&gt; ~200-500ms API+DDB&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Atomicity:&lt;/b&gt; turn-bound&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="310" y="170" width="260" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-cap" parent="p8c-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFECB3,#3a2e10);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;align=left;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="60-min streaming cap (AWS quota, non-adjustable)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="310" width="550" height="35" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-edge" parent="p8current" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;" edge="1" source="p8c-cli" target="p8c-rt">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-edge-l" connectable="0" parent="p8c-edge" style="edgeLabel;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;fontStyle=1;" value="SSE (one-way)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8c-summary" parent="p8current" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#2E7D32;html=1;align=left;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Pros:&lt;/b&gt; simple, works over plain HTTPS, browsers support natively via EventSource, passes firewalls transparently, AgentCore Runtime natively supports text/event-stream content-negotiation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cons:&lt;/b&gt; one-way (server→client only); client→server signals (nudge) need a separate REST round-trip; no mid-turn interrupt; 60-min cap per connection requires reconnect logic." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="580" width="900" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8proposed" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF8E1,#2a2618);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=3;strokeDasharray=8 4;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=16;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="PROPOSED Phase 1c — add /ws alongside /invocations" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1080" y="150" width="1060" height="620" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-cli" parent="p8proposed" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#232F3E;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="bgagent CLI&#xa;WebSocket client (new)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="70" width="230" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-rt" parent="p8proposed" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E0F2F1,#0d2838);strokeColor=#01A88D;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;container=1;collapsible=0;" value="Runtime-JWT microVM (same)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="340" y="70" width="680" height="500" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-srv" parent="p8p-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="server.py (unchanged)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;POST /invocations (SSE) — still works.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="40" width="290" height="75" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-ws" parent="p8p-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF8E1,#2a2618);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeDasharray=6 3;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#BF5700;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="server.py : /ws (NEW)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;WebSocket upgrade handshake.&lt;br&gt;Auth: same Cognito JWT via customJWTAuthorizer.&lt;br&gt;Wire: AG-UI events server→client; new client→server frames: NUDGE, CANCEL, INTERRUPT.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="140" width="290" height="170" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-pipe" parent="p8p-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="pipeline.py / runner.py (unchanged)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Sync bg thread. Still dual-emits to progress_writer + sse_adapter.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="340" y="40" width="310" height="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-hooks" parent="p8p-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF8E1,#2a2618);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#BF5700;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="hooks.py + ws_inbox (NEW)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Stop hook ALSO reads in-memory ws_inbox (asyncio.Queue per session).&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Same registry&lt;/b&gt; as Phase 2 _nudge_between_turns_hook — zero refactor.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="340" y="170" width="310" height="140" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-nudge-flow" parent="p8p-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#C925D1;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Nudge delivery path (if /ws available)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Client sends NUDGE frame on open socket → ws handler pushes to ws_inbox → Stop hook consumes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Latency:&lt;/b&gt; saves REST+DDB roundtrip (~200-500ms → ~10ms in-process).&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fallback:&lt;/b&gt; REST /tasks/{id}/nudge still works (Phase 2 path preserved).&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="330" width="630" height="130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-cap" parent="p8p-rt" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFECB3,#3a2e10);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;align=left;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="Still hits 60-min cap — WebSocket does NOT extend the streaming quota" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="470" width="630" height="25" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-edge" parent="p8proposed" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeDasharray=6 3;strokeWidth=2;startArrow=classic;endArrow=classic;" edge="1" source="p8p-cli" target="p8p-rt">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-edge-l" connectable="0" parent="p8p-edge" style="edgeLabel;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;fontStyle=1;" value="WebSocket (bidirectional)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8p-summary" parent="p8proposed" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#BF5700;html=1;align=left;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Pros:&lt;/b&gt; bidirectional; no REST roundtrip for nudges; mid-turn interrupt signaling channel; connection multiplexing (one open socket serves multiple concerns).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cons:&lt;/b&gt; more complex client (WebSocket state machine); some firewalls block WS upgrades; AgentCore /ws is currently in preview support tier (verify before commit); still hits 60-min cap; does not subsume REST — both must be maintained." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="580" width="1020" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8triggers" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFECB3,#3a2e10);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="Triggers to build Phase 1c (all must fire)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&quot;&gt;1. Phase 2 (nudge on REST, shipped) produces user-felt latency complaints — users report the ~500ms submit-to-visible latency as a friction point.&lt;br&gt;2. Phase 2.5 mid-turn interrupt (next page) becomes a near-term priority AND REST polling proves insufficient for the interrupt signal.&lt;br&gt;3. AgentCore /ws exits preview tier and is fully supported.&lt;br&gt;4. Client platforms that need WS (Web SPA dashboards, live collaboration) enter scope.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;Until all four are present, stay on SSE + REST. Complexity cost of WebSocket state machine is non-trivial." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="790" width="2100" height="200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8not" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFDE7,#2a2a14);strokeColor=#F9A825;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#6B4E00,#FFD180);spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b style=&quot;font-size:13px&quot;&gt;What Phase 1c is NOT&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;NOT a replacement for SSE.&lt;/b&gt; SSE stays as the primary streaming transport. /ws sits alongside for bidirectional cases.&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;NOT a replacement for REST nudge.&lt;/b&gt; REST stays as the submission path for non-connected clients (Slack bot, GitHub webhook, cron).&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;NOT a 60-min cap solution.&lt;/b&gt; WebSocket is still subject to the AWS-documented streaming cap.&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;NOT a requirement for Phase 2.5 or Phase 3.&lt;/b&gt; Both can be built on REST + SSE; /ws is a latency-and-ergonomics optimization." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1010" width="2100" height="200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p8legend" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#666666;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Legend&lt;/b&gt; — Green solid: current shipped (Phase 1b SSE). Orange dashed: proposed Phase 1c additions. Purple: existing DDB Phase 2 nudge path preserved." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1230" width="2100" height="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram name="9. Pending — Phase 2.5 mid-turn interrupt (proposal)" id="v5p9">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1709" dy="1009" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="0" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2200" pageHeight="1500" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="p9t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;" value="Pending — Phase 2.5: Mid-turn interrupt via ClaudeSDKClient.interrupt() (proposal)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="2100" x="40" y="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=13;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#555555;" value="Phase 2 delivers nudges between turns (post-tool-result, pre-next-turn). Phase 2.5 adds the ability to interrupt mid-turn — while a tool is running — via the existing Claude Agent SDK `client.interrupt()` call. Research during Phase 2 E2E confirmed this SDK capability exists TODAY; what&#39;s missing is the plumbing to trigger it from outside the agent container." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="2100" x="40" y="62" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9bar" parent="1" style="line;strokeWidth=2;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeDasharray=8 4;html=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="10" width="2100" x="40" y="120" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9arch" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF8E1,#2a2618);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="Proposed architecture — REST stop endpoint + agent stop_poller sibling task" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="520" width="2100" x="40" y="150" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-cli" parent="p9arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#232F3E;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="bgagent stop &lt;task_id&gt;&#xa;(NEW CLI command)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="200" x="30" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-api" parent="p9arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#EDE7F6,#1a1530);strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#8C4FFF;" value="API GW&#xa;POST /tasks/{id}/stop (NEW)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="220" x="270" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-lam" parent="p9arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF2E8,#2a1a0e);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;" value="StopTaskFn Lambda (NEW)&#xa;writes stop_requested=true" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="240" x="530" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-tt" parent="p9arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#C925D1;" value="TaskTable&#xa;(existing, new field:&#xa;stop_requested)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="200" x="810" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-agent" parent="p9arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E0F2F1,#0d2838);strokeColor=#01A88D;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#01A88D;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;" value="Agent container (existing + new stop_poller)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="440" width="1010" x="1060" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-client" parent="p9-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="ClaudeSDKClient (existing)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;• client.query() — standard turn loop&lt;br&gt;• client.interrupt() — CANCELS current turn ★ available today in SDK&lt;br&gt;• client.query(text) after interrupt → new turn with replacement instructions (&quot;redirect&quot;)&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="440" x="20" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-poller" parent="p9-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF8E1,#2a2618);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeDasharray=6 3;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#BF5700;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="stop_poller (NEW sibling asyncio task)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Spawned alongside runner; loops every 2-5s:&lt;br&gt;  row = GetItem(TaskTable, task_id)&lt;br&gt;  if row.stop_requested:&lt;br&gt;    await client.interrupt()&lt;br&gt;    drain remaining stream&lt;br&gt;    progress.write(turn_interrupted)&lt;br&gt;    if redirect: client.query(row.stop_instructions)&lt;br&gt;    else: close client, terminal stop&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="510" x="480" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-hooks" parent="p9-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="hooks.py (existing, reused)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Phase 2&#39;s between_turns_hooks registry ALREADY accommodates this pattern. Phase 2.5&#39;s stop_poller is a &lt;b&gt;sibling&lt;/b&gt; task, not a between-turns hook — it runs concurrently with the turn, not between turns.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="440" x="20" y="220" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9-tnote" parent="p9-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E3F2FD,#0d2238);strokeColor=#1F6FEB;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#1F6FEB;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="turn_interrupted event&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal&quot;&gt;Emit via progress_writer + sse_adapter (dual emission, same as Phase 2&#39;s nudge_acknowledged). Live watchers see ★ turn_interrupted. DDB has durable record.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="510" x="480" y="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e5" edge="1" parent="p9-agent" source="p9-poller" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#DD344C;strokeWidth=2.5;" target="p9-client">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e5l" connectable="0" parent="p9e5" style="edgeLabel;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#DD344C;fontStyle=1;" value="await client.interrupt()" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e1" edge="1" parent="p9arch" source="p9-cli" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;" target="p9-api">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e2" edge="1" parent="p9arch" source="p9-api" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;" target="p9-lam">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e3" edge="1" parent="p9arch" source="p9-lam" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;" target="p9-tt">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e3l" connectable="0" parent="p9e3" style="edgeLabel;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;fontStyle=1;" value="UpdateItem" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e4" edge="1" parent="p9arch" source="p9-tt" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;dashed=1;" target="p9-poller">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <Array as="points">
              <mxPoint x="1040" y="100" />
              <mxPoint x="1040" y="240" />
            </Array>
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9e4l" connectable="0" parent="p9e4" style="edgeLabel;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;fontStyle=1;" value="GetItem poll (2-5s)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9risks" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFEBEE,#3a1616);strokeColor=#DD344C;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#B00020,#FF8A80);container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="⚠ Risks / Known limitations" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="440" width="1040" x="40" y="700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9r1" parent="p9risks" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#DD344C;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#B00020,#FF8A80);spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;1. Side effects NOT rolled back&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;If `client.interrupt()` fires after a Bash command has already modified the filesystem or after an Edit has written a file, those changes persist. The SDK can&#39;t un-execute tool effects — it can only prevent further SDK-level actions." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="85" width="1000" x="20" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9r2" parent="p9risks" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#DD344C;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#B00020,#FF8A80);spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;2. Tool subprocess may outlive interrupt&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;If the agent has shelled out (e.g. long-running `pytest`), the subprocess keeps running until the AgentCore microVM is killed OR the tool respects the SDK&#39;s abort signal. MicroVM kill is an 8h worst case. Recommend bounded tool timeouts as a safety net." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="90" width="1000" x="20" y="145" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9r3" parent="p9risks" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#DD344C;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#B00020,#FF8A80);spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;3. Partial tool_use blocks in stream&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;The SSE stream may show a half-emitted TOOL_CALL_START without matching TOOL_CALL_END. Client rendering MUST handle orphan tool_use blocks gracefully (mark as &#39;interrupted&#39; in UI)." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="85" width="1000" x="20" y="245" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9r4" parent="p9risks" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#DD344C;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#B00020,#FF8A80);spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;4. Poll interval vs user expectation&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;stop_poller at 2-5s interval means up to 5s between stop request and interrupt. For faster reaction, Phase 1c /ws gives &lt;100ms ack; for slower, this interval is fine. Trade-off depends on user tolerance." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="1000" x="20" y="340" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9compat" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#C8E6C9,#1c361d);strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="✓ Phase 2 compatibility — between_turns_hooks was built to accommodate this" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="440" width="1040" x="1100" y="700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9c1" parent="p9compat" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#2E7D32;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;The registry is the abstraction.&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;Phase 2 introduced `between_turns_hooks: list[Hook]` in hooks.py. Each hook gets called with (ctx, turn_result). It returns Optional[dict] with SDK `decision`/`reason`. The registry is intentionally general — any new between-turns behavior (approval response, budget check, nudge delivery) plugs in without agent-loop refactor." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="1000" x="20" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9c2" parent="p9compat" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#2E7D32;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Phase 2.5&#39;s stop_poller is a SIBLING task (not a hook).&lt;/b&gt;&#xa;It runs CONCURRENTLY with the turn, calling client.interrupt() from outside the SDK&#39;s normal flow. This is by design — a between-turns hook fires AT a seam and cannot preempt a tool call in progress. The sibling task model is orthogonal and additive — Phase 2&#39;s hook registry keeps working unchanged." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="1000" x="20" y="180" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p9c3" parent="p9compat" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#2E7D32;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Research validated 2026-04-23:&lt;/b&gt; `ClaudeSDKClient.interrupt()` exists today in the SDK (confirmed by looking at the shipped Python package). Phase 2.5 is NOT waiting on SDK support — only on our own plumbing to wire it in." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="95" width="1000" x="20" y="320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram name="10. Pending — Phase 3 Cedar HITL approval (proposal)" id="v5p10">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1222" dy="824" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="0" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2200" pageHeight="1600" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="p10t" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#8C4FFF;" value="Pending — Phase 3: Cedar policy-driven HITL (replaces §9.3 3-tier design)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="2100" x="40" y="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10s" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=13;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#555555;" value="Sam+Alain agreement (2026-04-17):&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;the hardcoded 3-tier model (autonomous/smart/gated) in INTERACTIVE_AGENTS §9.3 is being replaced with Cedar policy-driven HITL.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Extend the existing agent Cedar engine (agent/src/policy.py) decision model from ALLOW/DENY to ALLOW/DENY/REQUIRE_APPROVAL.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Same policy language, broader semantics. Enables workflows like AI-DLC where users gate per phase and relax over time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;⚠ Design subject to final revision — see INTERACTIVE_AGENTS.md §9.3 pending update.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="75" width="2100" x="40" y="57" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10bar" parent="1" style="line;strokeWidth=2;strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeDasharray=8 4;html=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="10" width="2100" x="40" y="140" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10arch" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#EDE7F6,#1a1530);strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#8C4FFF;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="Architecture overview" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="640" width="2100" x="40" y="170" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-user" parent="p10arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#232F3E;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="User&#xa;bgagent approve &lt;task_id&gt; &lt;request_id&gt;&#xa;[--scope this_call|tool_type_session|…]" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="280" x="30" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-api" parent="p10arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#EDE7F6,#1a1530);strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#8C4FFF;" value="API GW&#xa;POST /tasks/{id}/approve (NEW)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="220" x="350" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-lam" parent="p10arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF2E8,#2a1a0e);strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#8C4FFF;" value="ApproveTaskFn Lambda (NEW)&#xa;writes decision + scope" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="240" x="610" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-at" parent="p10arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;strokeWidth=2;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#C925D1;" value="TaskApprovalsTable (NEW)&#xa;PK=task_id, SK=request_id (ULID)&#xa;attrs: decision, scope, author_sub, created_at, TTL 30d" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="300" x="890" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-agent" parent="p10arch" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#E0F2F1,#0d2838);strokeColor=#01A88D;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#01A88D;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;" value="Agent container — Cedar HITL extension" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="440" width="2040" x="30" y="170" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-cedar" parent="p10-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#EDE7F6,#1a1530);strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#8C4FFF;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="policy.py — Cedar engine (EXISTS, extended)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;Current: returns ALLOW | DENY.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;New in Phase 3:&lt;/b&gt; ALLOW | DENY | &lt;b&gt;REQUIRE_APPROVAL&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;Same Cedar policy language. Policies reference resource + action + context (user, repo, task_type, previously-approved scopes). Decision includes a human-readable reason.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Example policy:&lt;/b&gt; when action=Bash and resource matches &#39;rm -rf&#39; or &#39;DROP&#39; or &#39;git push --force&#39; → REQUIRE_APPROVAL.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="600" x="20" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-cut" parent="p10-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#01A88D;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#01A88D;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="can_use_tool SDK callback (NEW hook)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;Registered with ClaudeAgentOptions on client init. Fires BEFORE every tool invocation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Flow:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Call policy.evaluate(tool, args, ctx) → ALLOW | DENY | REQUIRE_APPROVAL.&lt;br&gt;2. If ALLOW: return — tool runs.&lt;br&gt;3. If DENY: return {decision:block, reason:policy_reason} — turn blocks.&lt;br&gt;4. If REQUIRE_APPROVAL: trigger approval flow (right side).&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="620" x="640" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-approval" parent="p10-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFF8E1,#2a2618);strokeColor=#BF5700;strokeWidth=2;strokeDasharray=6 3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#BF5700;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Approval flow (NEW)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;1. Emit approval_requested event (progress_writer + sse_adapter).&lt;br&gt;2. Set TaskTable.status = AWAITING_APPROVAL (new state).&lt;br&gt;3. Poll TaskApprovalsTable every 2-5s for row with matching request_id.&lt;br&gt;4a. Approved → cache scope decision in in-memory allowlist; return permit → SDK runs tool.&lt;br&gt;4b. Denied → return {decision:block, reason:user_denied}.&lt;br&gt;4c. Timeout 5 min → fail-closed DENY, emit approval_timeout.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="740" x="1280" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-scopes" parent="p10-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#8C4FFF;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#8C4FFF;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Escalation scopes (from §9.4)&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;• &lt;b&gt;this_call&lt;/b&gt; — approve only this specific invocation&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;tool_type_session&lt;/b&gt; — approve all future calls to this tool type for the rest of the session (e.g. all Bash)&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;tool_type_pattern&lt;/b&gt; — approve calls matching a pattern (e.g. Bash matching &#39;git *&#39;)&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;all_session&lt;/b&gt; — switch to autonomous mode for the rest of the session&lt;br&gt;Scope cached in in-memory allowlist; next can_use_tool check short-circuits REQUIRE_APPROVAL.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="1240" x="20" y="270" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10-statenote" parent="p10-agent" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#C925D1;spacing=8;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="New task state: AWAITING_APPROVAL&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&quot;&gt;Transitions:&lt;br&gt;  RUNNING → AWAITING_APPROVAL (approval_requested emitted)&lt;br&gt;  AWAITING_APPROVAL → RUNNING (approval received)&lt;br&gt;  AWAITING_APPROVAL → FAILED (timeout or deny)&lt;br&gt;Fan-out plane notifies Slack/GitHub of AWAITING_APPROVAL via DDB Stream.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="740" x="1280" y="270" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10e1" edge="1" parent="p10arch" source="p10-user" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;" target="p10-api">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10e2" edge="1" parent="p10arch" source="p10-api" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;" target="p10-lam">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10e3" edge="1" parent="p10arch" source="p10-lam" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;" target="p10-at">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10e4" edge="1" parent="p10arch" source="p10-at" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;strokeColor=#8C4FFF;strokeWidth=2;dashed=1;" target="p10-approval">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <Array as="points">
              <mxPoint x="1040" y="150" />
              <mxPoint x="1650" y="150" />
            </Array>
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10e4l" connectable="0" parent="p10e4" style="edgeLabel;html=1;fontSize=10;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#8C4FFF;fontStyle=1;" value="agent polls" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10note" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFDE7,#2a2a14);strokeColor=#F9A825;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#6B4E00,#FFD180);spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="⚠ Design subject to final Cedar-HITL revision — see INTERACTIVE_AGENTS.md §9.3 pending update&#xa;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&quot;&gt;The 3-tier design (autonomous/smart/gated) documented in §9.3 is being REPLACED. The replacement — Cedar-driven HITL — is agreed in principle (Sam+Alain 2026-04-17) but detailed spec is not yet landed in INTERACTIVE_AGENTS.md. This diagram shows the proposed direction, not a final design. Review with Sam before implementation.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="2100" x="40" y="830" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10why" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#C8E6C9,#1c361d);strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="Why Cedar-driven instead of hardcoded tiers" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="300" width="1040" x="40" y="960" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10why-b" parent="p10why" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#2E7D32;html=1;align=left;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="• &lt;b&gt;Reuses existing engine.&lt;/b&gt; policy.py is already in production (Phase 1a). No new policy runtime.&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;Policy-as-code.&lt;/b&gt; Gated behaviors are configurable per repo / per user / per blueprint without code changes.&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;AI-DLC workflow fit.&lt;/b&gt; Users can gate PLAN phase strictly, then relax for BUILD once trust established — expressible in Cedar.&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;Audit trail built-in.&lt;/b&gt; Cedar decisions logged with full context. Compliance-friendly.&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;Deterministic + fast.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;1ms per check vs LLM-based classifier (1-2s, $).&#xa;• &lt;b&gt;Auditable.&lt;/b&gt; Cedar policies are human-readable; can be reviewed + version-controlled in the repo." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="240" width="1000" x="20" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10deps" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFECB3,#3a2e10);strokeColor=#F9A825;strokeWidth=2;html=1;verticalAlign=top;fontStyle=1;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);container=1;collapsible=0;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;" value="Prerequisites" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="300" width="1040" x="1100" y="960" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10deps-b" parent="p10deps" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#FFFFFF,#1a1a1a);strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;align=left;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=light-dark(#BF5700,#FFD180);spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="1. INTERACTIVE_AGENTS §9.3 revision landed — final Cedar-HITL spec.&#xa;2. Phase 2 (nudge) validated in production for ≥1 week — establishes the between-turns infrastructure pattern.&#xa;3. Cedar policy schema extended with REQUIRE_APPROVAL outcome (needs Cedar policy language verification — confirm cedar-agent Python library supports custom outcomes or use allow/deny + context flag).&#xa;4. CLI approval UX reviewed with early users (bgagent approve command ergonomics).&#xa;5. Fail-closed timeout semantics agreed: 5-min default, configurable per Blueprint, emits approval_timeout → DENY.&#xa;6. Testing plan: unit tests for policy engine, integration tests for the approval round-trip, E2E test that reproduces an AI-DLC flow." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="240" width="1000" x="20" y="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p10fanout" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5E6F7,#2a1a2f);strokeColor=#C925D1;strokeWidth=1;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#C925D1;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;b&gt;Non-CLI channels automatically handled via fan-out plane:&lt;/b&gt; AWAITING_APPROVAL state change + approval_requested event surface through TaskEventsTable DDB Stream to FanOutFn → Slack DM the approver / GitHub PR comment / SES email. Approval responses come back through the same API (POST /approve), which works from any channel with a Cognito JWT. No new fan-out infrastructure needed — reuses Phase 1b." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="2100" x="40" y="1280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram name="11. Decision rationale (updated with Phase 2 validations)" id="v5p11">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1937" dy="1144" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="0" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2000" pageHeight="2280" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="p7-0" />
        <mxCell id="p7-1" parent="p7-0" />
        <mxCell id="p7-t" parent="p7-1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=26;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="Decision rationale — Phase 1b + Phase 2, chosen vs rejected options (all validated in production)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="1900" x="40" y="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-ts" parent="p7-1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=13;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#555555;" value="Top section — Phase 1b (D1 auth/runtime, D2 server.py SSE, D3 CLI SSE client): chosen option highlighted green with a star, rejected options grayed with &quot;why rejected&quot;, validation status appended after 2026-04-22 re-validation. Bottom section — Phase 2 ⭐ (D4 rate-limit-after-guardrail, D5 between-turns hook registry, D6 TaskNudgesTable, D7 observability-first delivery): same chosen/rejected/status shape, validated 2026-04-23 E2E." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="60" width="1900" x="40" y="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-sec1-lbl" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#E8EAF6;strokeColor=#3F51B5;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#1A237E;fontFamily=Helvetica;spacing=12;" value="Phase 1b decisions (validated in production 2026-04-22 + 2026-04-23)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="38" width="1900" x="40" y="130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-bar" parent="p7-1" style="line;strokeWidth=2;strokeColor=#666666;html=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="10" width="1900" x="40" y="178" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d1h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#232F3E;strokeColor=#232F3E;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="D1 — Auth/runtime split" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="620" x="40" y="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d2h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#232F3E;strokeColor=#232F3E;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="D2 — server.py SSE architecture" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="620" x="680" y="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d3h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#232F3E;strokeColor=#232F3E;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="D3 — CLI SSE client" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="620" x="1320" y="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d1-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Two AgentCore Runtimes from same Docker image&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;• Runtime-IAM (orchestrator path, SigV4 from Lambda)&lt;br&gt;• Runtime-JWT (direct CLI SSE, customJWTAuthorizer→Cognito JWKS)&lt;br&gt;• Sessions scoped to one runtime ARN; not transferable&lt;br&gt;• ProgressWriter writes DDB regardless of runtime, so cross-path observation works (polling); cross-path control does not&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why chosen:&lt;/b&gt; AgentCore authorizerConfiguration is mutually exclusive. Two runtimes = cleanest solution. Same image = zero code delta. 2x runtime cost acceptable for Phase 1b.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Status:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;VALIDATED IN PRODUCTION 2026-04-22 + 2026-04-23&lt;/span&gt; — both runtimes reached READY; Cognito JWT auth on Runtime-JWT verified live; SigV4 on Runtime-IAM via OrchestratorFn verified; cross-path DDB observation works.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="400" width="620" x="40" y="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d1-r1" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Option B — API Gateway bridge Lambda&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Single runtime; JWT→SigV4 bridge Lambda in front.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;API GW 29s hard timeout is fatal for SSE. Would need Lambda response streaming + custom proxying. Bridge Lambda is a new failure point. Lambda 15-min hard timeout conflicts with 60-min SSE cap.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="620" x="40" y="700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d1-r2" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Option C — Reuse single Runtime-IAM; CLI signs SigV4&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Have the CLI do SigV4 signing directly from user credentials.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Requires every CLI user to have AWS credentials with InvokeAgentRuntime IAM. Breaks principle of user-identity-based auth. Painful onboarding; conflicts with Cognito-based identity model.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="620" x="40" y="890" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d2-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Background thread + asyncio.Queue bridge&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;• Sync run_task stays in bg thread (no Phase 1a regression)&lt;br&gt;• New SSEAdapter is sibling to ProgressWriter&lt;br&gt;• Both receive same events at every emission point&lt;br&gt;• ProgressWriter → DDB (durability)&lt;br&gt;• SSEAdapter → per-session asyncio.Queue&lt;br&gt;• server.py SSE endpoint drains Queue, emits AG-UI frames + : ping\n\n every 15s&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why chosen:&lt;/b&gt; Preserves deployed sync code. Low blast radius. Claude SDK integration already works synchronously — don&#39;t fix what isn&#39;t broken.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Status:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;VALIDATED IN PRODUCTION&lt;/span&gt; — 442 → 453 agent tests still green; orchestrator Lambda path byte-for-byte unchanged; SSE handler drains queue correctly over 60-min cap.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="400" width="620" x="680" y="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d2-r1" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Option A — Inline async generator (full rewrite)&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Convert run_task + pipeline.py + runner.py to async generators; yield events all the way up.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Every yield propagates up the stack. Requires refactoring working Phase 1a code. Claude SDK would need async validation. Large regression surface. Backpressure nice in theory but not worth the churn.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="620" x="680" y="700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d2-r2" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Option C — Poll ProgressWriter from SSE endpoint&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Have SSE endpoint poll DDB Table and forward new events.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Polls DDB inside agent — wasteful. Latency equals poll interval (the very thing SSE is supposed to fix). Each SSE connection adds DDB load. Defeats the purpose of streaming entirely.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="620" x="680" y="890" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d3-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Hybrid: @ag-ui/core types + native fetch/eventsource-parser transport&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;• Import @ag-ui/core for 17 event TYPES + Zod SCHEMAS only&lt;br&gt;• Own the transport: native fetch + eventsource-parser (32.7M wk downloads)&lt;br&gt;• CLI wrapper: exp backoff reconnect, JWT refresh, 60-min stream restart, dedupe buffer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why chosen:&lt;/b&gt; Bets on the stable wire format (14+ frameworks adopted). Insulates from 0.0.x runtime churn. Matches AWS FAST template pattern. No HttpAgent wrapping required.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Status:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;VALIDATED IN PRODUCTION&lt;/span&gt; — SSE primary + REST polling fallback + REST catch-up after reconnect all exercised live; 60-min restart path tested (implicit in long-running Phase 2 E2E tasks).&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="400" width="620" x="1320" y="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d3-r1" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Option A — Full @ag-ui/client HttpAgent&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Use the official client library and wrap HttpAgent with our reconnect logic.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;@ag-ui/client is 0.0.x pre-1.0. Single-shot request model, no built-in reconnect/backoff/token-refresh. We&#39;d wrap it anyway. Every version bump is a breaking-change risk.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="620" x="1320" y="700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d3-r2" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Option B — Pure native fetch, no AG-UI deps&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Copy the 17 event type definitions into cli/src/types.ts manually.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Forever-growing type parity burden. AG-UI went from 4 to 16 types in 2025. Hand-maintained Zod schemas drift from spec. Better to consume the authoritative package for the data model and own only the transport.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="620" x="1320" y="890" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-summary" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#FFECB3;strokeColor=#F9A825;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#BF5700;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="Common thread across all three Phase 1b chosen options&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Lowest regression risk:&lt;/b&gt; each choice preserves the Phase 1a behavior that is already deployed and working&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Bet on stable interfaces, not unstable runtimes:&lt;/b&gt; AgentCore auth config (stable), AG-UI wire format (stable), eventsource-parser (mature), vs. @ag-ui/client (0.0.x, churning)&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Additive, not replacive:&lt;/b&gt; new runtime next to old, new adapter next to existing writer, new streaming plane next to polling plane. No &quot;rip and replace.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="1900" x="40" y="1080" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-sec2-lbl" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#FFF3E0;strokeColor=#E65100;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#BF5700;fontFamily=Helvetica;spacing=12;" value="⭐ Phase 2 decisions (validated in production 2026-04-23 E2E — interactive nudge)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="38" width="1900" x="40" y="1220" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-bar2" parent="p7-1" style="line;strokeWidth=2;strokeColor=#E65100;html=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="10" width="1900" x="40" y="1268" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d4h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#BF5700;strokeColor=#BF5700;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="⭐ D4 — Rate-limit AFTER guardrail (not before)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="940" x="40" y="1300" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d5h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#BF5700;strokeColor=#BF5700;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="⭐ D5 — Between-turns hook registry (Phase 2.5 + 3 reuse)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="940" x="1020" y="1300" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d4-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Guardrail BEFORE rate-limit counter increment&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Decision:&lt;/b&gt; In &lt;code&gt;cdk/src/handlers/nudge-task.ts&lt;/code&gt;, preflight order is: auth → validation → ownership → state gate → &lt;b&gt;Bedrock Guardrail → rate-limit counter increment → persist&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rationale:&lt;/b&gt; If a guardrail-blocked message consumed a rate-limit slot, an attacker (or well-meaning user writing policy-violating messages) could lock themselves out of legitimate nudges by burning the 10/min budget on blocked submissions. Guardrail-first means only &lt;i&gt;successful&lt;/i&gt; submissions count against the rate limit — blocked submissions are &quot;free&quot; so the user can correct and retry without waiting out the window.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="260" width="940" x="40" y="1370" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d4-rej" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Alternative — Rate-limit first, guardrail second&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Simpler ordering: check the counter before paying the Bedrock call cost.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Inverts the cost model — blocked submissions would consume a slot they never got value from. Attackers or users iterating on wording could brick their own nudge budget for the next 60s. The cost of a Bedrock guardrail call is trivial vs. the UX damage of &quot;your bad words used up your rate limit.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="940" x="40" y="1640" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d4-status" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#1B5E20;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;VALIDATED 2026-04-23&lt;/span&gt;  Solo test T8&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Sent 11 rapid nudges after 1 guardrail-blocked submission. The blocked submission did NOT consume a slot; the 11th (not the 10th) was rate-limited with 429. If ordering were inverted only 9 successes would have landed.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="940" x="40" y="1780" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d5-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Module-level between_turns_hooks registry in agent/src/hooks.py&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Decision:&lt;/b&gt; Expose &lt;code&gt;between_turns_hooks: list[BetweenTurnsHook]&lt;/code&gt; as a module-level registry. Phase 2&#39;s &lt;code&gt;_nudge_between_turns_hook&lt;/code&gt; is the first and currently only entry. The SDK Stop hook (&lt;code&gt;stop_hook&lt;/code&gt;) iterates the list and joins returned text chunks into &lt;code&gt;{&quot;decision&quot;: &quot;block&quot;, &quot;reason&quot;: &quot;...&quot;}&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rationale:&lt;/b&gt; Phase 3 (approval gate resumption) and any other future Stop-seam logic can &lt;code&gt;append&lt;/code&gt; their own hooks without touching the Stop hook callback itself. The ctx dict threading &lt;code&gt;task_id + progress + sse_adapter&lt;/code&gt; gives every hook observability without module-global state.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Phase 2.5 compatibility:&lt;/b&gt; Phase 2.5 mid-turn interrupt is orthogonal (sibling asyncio task polling stop flag, not a Stop-hook addition) but the same ctx dict threading pattern applies.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="260" width="940" x="1020" y="1370" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d5-rej" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Alternative — Hard-code nudge injection directly in stop_hook callback&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Inline the nudge reader call inside the Stop hook with no indirection.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Phase 3 approval resumption and any other Stop-seam consumer would force edits to the same callback, creating merge conflicts and a growing switch-statement anti-pattern. Registry design costs nothing at runtime and unblocks Phase 3 architecturally.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="940" x="1020" y="1640" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d5-status" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#1B5E20;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;DESIGN VALIDATED BY PHASE 2 SHIPPING&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Phase 3 implementation unblocked architecturally — new consumers can append to the registry without touching the Stop hook callback. ctx dict threading verified end-to-end 2026-04-23.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="940" x="1020" y="1780" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d6h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#BF5700;strokeColor=#BF5700;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="⭐ D6 — TaskNudgesTable separate from TaskTable" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="940" x="40" y="1905" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d7h" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#BF5700;strokeColor=#BF5700;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=16;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontFamily=Helvetica;" value="⭐ D7 — Observability-first nudge delivery (milestone emission)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="55" width="940" x="1020" y="1905" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d6-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Dedicated TaskNudgesTable (not a nested attr on TaskTable)&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Decision:&lt;/b&gt; Phase 2 introduces a dedicated DDB table rather than sharing TaskTable.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rationale:&lt;/b&gt; (a) Nudges use a distinct PK/SK structure (PK=task_id, SK=nudge_id ULID) that does not compose cleanly with TaskTable&#39;s single-item-per-task model; (b) nudge rows carry a conditional-update contract (&lt;code&gt;consumed=false&lt;/code&gt; for at-most-once delivery) incompatible with TaskTable&#39;s frequent status churn — the two should not contend; (c) rate-limit counter rows live in the same table with their own ~2-minute TTL, distinct from nudge rows&#39; 30-day TTL — easier to manage on a dedicated table.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="260" width="940" x="40" y="1975" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d6-rej" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Alternative — Nested list attribute on the TaskTable record&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Store nudges as &lt;code&gt;nudges: [...]&lt;/code&gt; on the task item; one less table to provision.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;DDB UpdateItem on a list attribute is non-atomic at the list-element level. Concurrent nudge submissions would clobber each other. Also mixes two TTLs and two update cadences onto one hot item.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="940" x="40" y="2245" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d6-status" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#1B5E20;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;LIVE IN PRODUCTION&lt;/span&gt;  With PITR&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Conditional UpdateItem with ExpressionAttributeNames alias for the &lt;code&gt;consumed&lt;/code&gt; reserved keyword verified working against real DDB 2026-04-23.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="940" x="40" y="2385" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d7-chosen" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#C8E6C9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=3;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;spacing=12;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="★ CHOSEN — Synthetic agent_milestone on nudge_acknowledged, dual-emit to DDB + SSE&#xa;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:11px&#39;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Decision:&lt;/b&gt; When a nudge is applied at the Stop seam, &lt;code&gt;agent/src/hooks.py&lt;/code&gt; emits a synthetic &lt;code&gt;agent_milestone(milestone=&quot;nudge_acknowledged&quot;, details=&quot;N nudge(s) applied (ids=…XXX): &amp;lt;preview&amp;gt;&quot;)&lt;/code&gt; event to BOTH &lt;code&gt;progress_writer&lt;/code&gt; (durable, DDB audit) AND &lt;code&gt;sse_adapter&lt;/code&gt; (live stream) — best-effort, never blocks the nudge injection itself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rationale:&lt;/b&gt; Without this, the operator nudging the agent has no way to know their nudge reached the agent until the next tool call reflects it. A visible ★ nudge_acknowledged stream marker closes that feedback loop in real time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Design nuance:&lt;/b&gt; Emit fires on the successful-injection path only — empty-pending state does NOT emit (avoids log spam). Emit failures are swallowed so a flaky writer cannot block nudge delivery.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="260" width="940" x="1020" y="1975" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d7-rej" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=light-dark(#F5F5F5,#2a2a2a);strokeColor=#999999;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#666666;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;text-decoration:line-through&#39;&gt;Alternative — Silent injection; user infers from next tool call&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;No milestone emission — keep the nudge path as a pure side-effect on the agent&#39;s next message.&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&#xa;&lt;b&gt;Rejected:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&#39;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Opaque UX — the user sees nothing between &quot;sent nudge&quot; and &quot;agent eventually reacts.&quot; Dual-emit is best-effort and swallowed on failure, so the observability upside costs nothing on the happy path and zero on the failure path.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="940" x="1020" y="2245" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p7-d7-status" parent="p7-1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#E8F5E9;strokeColor=#2E7D32;strokeWidth=2;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#1B5E20;spacing=10;whiteSpace=wrap;fontStyle=1;" value="&lt;span style=&#39;background-color:#2E7D32;color:#FFFFFF;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px&#39;&gt;LIVE AND USER-VALIDATED 2026-04-23&lt;/span&gt;&#xa;&lt;span style=&#39;font-weight:normal;font-size:10px&#39;&gt;Both Nudge-A (interactive/JWT) and Nudge-B (orchestrator/IAM) surfaced the ★ nudge_acknowledged marker end-to-end.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="100" width="940" x="1020" y="2385" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
